arts.ttl: Milan Player Ratings vs Empoli: Reijnders Reigns Supreme
arts.sum: Paulo Fonseca's side took advantage of a foggy evening in Milan to return to winning ways in Serie A with a commanding 3-0 home win against bottom-half Empoli. Tijjani Reijnders stole the spotlight at Stadio San Siro with yet another brace this season, helping the Rossoneri arrest a two-game winless league streak. arts.ttl: Paulo Fonseca: ‘We could have scored 6 or 7 goals’
arts.sum: Following AC Milan’s impressive victory against Empoli, coach Paulo Fonseca shared his thoughts on the match during a post-game interview with DAZN. He expressed his satisfaction with the team’s performance, despite some frustrations regarding officiating. Fonseca began by acknowledging his irritation with the referee, stating, “I was very angry with the referee, but I want to move on. We played a beautiful game, both offensively and defensively. Chukwueze came on and contributed well, showing great sacrifice for the team. We scored three goals but could have easily netted six or seven, and we need to improve in that area. arts.ttl: Serie A | Milan 3-0 Empoli: Match Report
arts.sum: AC Milan secured a convincing 3-0 win over Empoli at a foggy San Siro, with Tijjani Reijnders making a significant impact by scoring two goals. The match began with Alvaro Morata putting Milan ahead, setting the stage for a much-needed victory as the Rossoneri aimed to bounce back from a series of mixed results in Serie A. Coming off a thrilling 3-2 Champions League triumph against Slovan Bratislava, Milan was eager to improve their performance in the league after drawing their last two matches against Cagliari and Juventus. arts.ttl: Reijnders shines through the fog at San Siro as Milan beats Empoli
arts.sum: Milan doubled its tally on the stroke of halftime when a cross was flicked on by Christian Pulisic and fell to Reijnders, who let it bounce before smashing it into the bottom left corner on the half volley. Como and Monza remain mired in the relegation zone after a hard-fought derby that finished 1-1.
